Get ready to start the game!

Thank you for reading the instructions. Get ready start with the 40 rounds of this game.

If you need to take a break, feel free to take one after the end of a round, before continuing to the next one.

Remember, the more money the spider gets, the bigger your bonus will be!

Press space to begin.


(If, at any point, the space key does not take you to the next page, click once on the text and try again.)

response.Q3: The cost for clicking on nodes varied between nodes.

response.Q0: Click on the furthest-away nodes, find the highest value node I could out of those ones, and then chart a course to navigate the spider to that node.
response.Q1: The first couple of rounds, I clicked on basically every node. After about round 3, I kind of realised that was a waste of money; I didn't get rewarded for clicking on nodes (cash added) nearly as much as I got 'punished' by having cash subtracted. So after that, I focused solely on clicking around the furthest-away nodes. If I found a node that was +40 or higher I'd head there, figuring that there was only 1 route to get to each node and I'd always come out with a positive cash result that way.
response.Q2: Somewhat difficult; the highest-value nodes weren't in the same place every time, or clustered together, so it was kind of hard to guess in advance where they'd be and navigate towards them without clicking around a lot

response.Q0: Not really; I probably should have clicked on more nodes at the 'first level' rather than writing off clicking on these nodes as pointless
